  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Cargo Officer (Bunker)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Role:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Manage cargo operations and documentation</li>\n  <li>Safeguard product quality and quantity</li>\n  <li>Ensure all cargo loading, ex bunker delivery, blending operation and delivery are<br>\nin compliance with Company work instructions and in particular SS648: 2024,<br>\nwherever applicable.</li>\n  <li>Ensure that custody control procedures in respect of cargo storage onboard<br>\nbunker tanker and cargo movements are duly and properly implemented.</li>\n  <li>Maintain proper and timely records of inventory in the stock movement logbook<br>\nand daily ROB report.</li>\n  <li>Report on any customer complaint or dispute to the Operations Manager<br>\nimmediately and assist in onsite investigation.</li>\n  <li>Any other ad-hoc duties as assigned.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>1 Year Experience as bunker clerk/cargo officer onboard bunker tankers.</li>\n  <li>Certification in Basic &amp; Advanced Course on Bunkering Practices (SS600 &amp; TR<br>\n48).</li>\n  <li>Certification in Code of Practice for Bunker Mass Flow Metering (SS 648:2024).</li>\n  <li>Willingness to follow Company’s shift duties and stay onboard vessel.</li>\n  <li>Effective communication skills.</li>\n  <li>Meticulous, responsible and good follow through skills</li>\n</ul>",
